 <text>
  <front>
   <head>SONG.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quintet">
     <l n="1" met="--+|--+" line_length="6">WHEN thy Beauty appears</l>
     <l n="2" met="--+|--+" line_length="6">In its Graces and Airs,</l>
     <l n="3" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">All bright as an Angel new dropt from the Sky;</l>
     <l n="4" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">At distance I gaze, and am aw'd by my Fears,</l>
     <l n="5" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">So strangely you dazzle my Eye!</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quintet">
     <l n="6" met="--+|--+" line_length="6">But when without Art,</l>
     <l n="7" met="--+|--+" line_length="6">Your kind Thoughts you impart,</l>
     <l n="8" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">When your Love runs in Blushes thro' ev'ry Vein;</l>
     <l n="9" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">When it darts from your Eyes, when it pants in your Heart,</l>
     <l n="10" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">Then I know you're a Woman again.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quintet">
     <l n="11" met="--+|--+" line_length="6">There's a Passion and Pride</l>
     <l n="12" met="--+|--+" line_length="6">In our Sex, (she reply'd,)</l>
     <l n="13" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">And thus (might I gratify both) I wou'd do:</l>
     <l n="14" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">Still an Angel appear to each Lover beside,</l>
     <l n="15" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">But still be a Woman to you.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
